<subSubSection lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="80" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1765,2006]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,329,1765,1790]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">Type material.</emphasis>
Describing 
<taxonomicName authority="Suffrian (1866)" authorityName="Suffrian" authorityYear="1866" box="[474,790,1765,1790]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spilotus">
<emphasis box="[474,602,1765,1789]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">M. spilotus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Suffrian, E." box="[613,790,1765,1790]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 483" refId="ref45438" refString="Suffrian, E. (1866) Zur Kenntniss der Sudamerikanischen Cryptocephalen. Linnaea Entomologica, 16, 1 - 483." type="journal article" year="1866">Suffrian (1866)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
wrote: “ 
<collectingCountry box="[894,997,1765,1790]" name="Brazil" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">Brasilien</collectingCountry>
(Mus. Schaum) ... in einem einzigen stücke ... 
<specimenCount box="[258,279,1802,1825]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
unbekannt”. Therefore, the female housed in 
<collectionCode box="[796,900,1802,1825]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">MNHUB</collectionCode>
and labelled: “America, collect. Schaum” must be considered the 
<typeStatus box="[356,454,1837,1862]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">holotype</typeStatus>
of the species. Anyway, there is not a complete correspondence between the label data and what Suffrian registered in his monography (see also what has been said on the subject in relation to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Suffrian" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corruptus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">M. corruptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In my opinion this shows that in identifying the types of the species described by Suffrian, it is necessary to interpret wisely the information available, without persisting too much in the search of a complete correspondence between the different sources.
</paragraph>
