<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82">
Female. Habitus in 
<figureCitation box="[423,489,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[204,1399,193,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[185,1409,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. M. languidus (7), M. spilotus (8). 7a–b: habitus; 7c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [1.0 mm]; 7f: sclerites II–III–IV of endophallus [0.8 mm]; 7g: sclerite I and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.8 mm]; 7h: spermatheca [1.0 mm]; 7k–m: rectal apparatus in dorsal (k) and ventral (m) view [1.0 mm]. 8a–b: habitus; 8c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [1.1 mm]; 8f: sclerites II–III–IV of endophallus [0.7 mm]; 8g: sclerite I and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.7 mm]; 8h: spermatheca [0.8 mm]; 8k–m: rectal apparatus in dorsal (k) and ventral (m) view [1.0 mm]. 7a–b: lectotype; 8a–b: holotype. Square brackets: length of scale segment." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3066644/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="82">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
a–b (HT). BL = 
<quantity box="[681,771,151,176]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" unit="mm" value="5.4">5.4 mm</quantity>
, BW = 
<quantity box="[863,952,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
, PL = 
<quantity box="[1032,1121,151,176]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
, PW = 
<quantity box="[1210,1301,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
. Interocular distance 12.0% of BL. In the only female examined pronotal black patch almost split in two roughly squared spots by a narrow, longitudinal, deep constriction.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82">
Fifth abdominal ventrite in females with a slightly transverse and rather deep pit. Vasculum of spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[159,242,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[204,1399,193,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[185,1409,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. M. languidus (7), M. spilotus (8). 7a–b: habitus; 7c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [1.0 mm]; 7f: sclerites II–III–IV of endophallus [0.8 mm]; 7g: sclerite I and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.8 mm]; 7h: spermatheca [1.0 mm]; 7k–m: rectal apparatus in dorsal (k) and ventral (m) view [1.0 mm]. 8a–b: habitus; 8c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [1.1 mm]; 8f: sclerites II–III–IV of endophallus [0.7 mm]; 8g: sclerite I and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.7 mm]; 8h: spermatheca [0.8 mm]; 8k–m: rectal apparatus in dorsal (k) and ventral (m) view [1.0 mm]. 7a–b: lectotype; 8a–b: holotype. Square brackets: length of scale segment." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3066644/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="82">Fig. 8h</figureCitation>
) with lower branch slightly curved and faintly swollen at base, and the upper one straight and regularly tapered in an acute, faintly pigmented apex. Insertions of gland and duct dorsally placed, fairly pigmented. Duct rather tightly coiled in proximal and median part. Non-coiled section rather long. Insertion on bursa copulatrix not swollen, not pigmented. Rectal apparatus (
<figureCitation box="[638,705,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[204,1399,193,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[185,1409,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. M. languidus (7), M. spilotus (8). 7a–b: habitus; 7c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [1.0 mm]; 7f: sclerites II–III–IV of endophallus [0.8 mm]; 7g: sclerite I and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.8 mm]; 7h: spermatheca [1.0 mm]; 7k–m: rectal apparatus in dorsal (k) and ventral (m) view [1.0 mm]. 8a–b: habitus; 8c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [1.1 mm]; 8f: sclerites II–III–IV of endophallus [0.7 mm]; 8g: sclerite I and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.7 mm]; 8h: spermatheca [0.8 mm]; 8k–m: rectal apparatus in dorsal (k) and ventral (m) view [1.0 mm]. 7a–b: lectotype; 8a–b: holotype. Square brackets: length of scale segment." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3066644/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="82">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
k–m) with dorsal sclerites quite deep, regularly tapered towards median line, with apodemes apparent, hyaline, above all towards outer rim. Ventral sclerite narrow, barely tapered on sides, lighter on its central section, with apodemes small, rounded, scarcely protruding.
</paragraph>
